  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*:\r\nAmount from unsuccessful attempt to sign transaction is sent if trigger another transaction and sign it with correct password.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nIf new transaction is initiated then data is used for this new transaction, not from previous one\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nAmount from previous attempt to sign transaction with wrong password is sent when new transaction with other amount is signed with correct password\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nsee from 00:18 https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8486364/sessions/4393851190/?accessToken=Zkyymys0L36x2oS25MWsUZYcHDM\r\ngeth log: \r\n[other tx geth.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/2095604/other.tx.geth.log)\r\n\r\n1.  in 1:1 chat: use /send 0.04 ETH \r\n2. on Send transaction screen provide wrong password and tap Sign transaction. As a result, error \"Wrong password\" is shown\r\n3. use \"<\" button or device back button on Android to return to same 1:1 chat. \r\n4. in same 1:1 chat use /send 0.000013 ETH and tap send button\r\n5. Note that Send Transaction screen will be shown with Wrong password error. This is probably when it gets wrong.\r\n6. Provide valid password and tap send\r\n\r\nAs a result, 1:1 chat contains second message with 0.000013 ETH but in fact 0.4 ETH is sent\r\n![chat](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/41312504-83d3a21c-6e87-11e8-95f5-e1725fe6c0de.png)\r\n![history](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/41312514-8714e7f6-6e87-11e8-8e79-e9fdd13217d7.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: nightly june 12\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote><div><strong><a href=\"https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803622-status/builds/8486364/sessions/4393851190/?accessToken=Zkyymys0L36x2oS25MWsUZYcHDM\">TestFairy: Status 0.9.19 (6047) @152</a></strong></div></blockquote>",
